
WEEK 1 — SECURITY ASSESSMENT REPORT
Name: Anam Batool  DHC-4272
Application Tested
Name: OWASP Juice Shop
URL: http://localhost:3000
Purpose: Web Security Testing Lab
Vulnerabilities Found                                                                                                                                                                  1. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
Description: The app executes injected JavaScript input.
Proof: <script>alert('XSS');</script> triggered popup.
2. Weak Password Policy                                                                                                                                             Description: The app allows very weak passwords like 12345.
Secure Areas                                                                                                                                                                SQL Injection Test                                                                                                                                                             Result: Login bypass attempt failed.

Areas of Improvement
•	Input validation and output encoding
•	Strong password enforcement
•	Secure authentication handling
•	Web security best practices
________________________________________
Conclusion
The application contains security weaknesses that require improvement, especially in input sanitization and password security.


